      <arrangement id="aspace_arr1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>In 10 folders as follows: 1. Information regarding Sigrid Schultz. 2. Biographical information. 3. Correspondence. 4. Personal effects. 5. Official documents. 6. Clippings. 7. Passports. 8. Part books. 9. Miscellaneous. 10. Opera bills.</p>
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_sc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Joseph Jaskewitz Papers document the career of the Austrian operatic singer and director through detailed performance diaries and partbooks used in the preparation of his roles, as well as personal effects, opera bills, photographs, and miscellaneous materials.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_bh1">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Joseph Jaskewitz was born on January 5, 1808 in Vienna. He began his opera career there as a choral singer in 1827, but soon he was performing solo roles in Zagreb (Agram), Budapest, Linz, Mainz, Frankfurt, and Aachen. In 1840 he joined the Hoftheater in Wiesbaden, and he became its director in 1855. He remained at the Hoftheater until his retirement in 1878. The date of his death is uncertain. According to an article in the <emph render="italic">Wiesbadener Tagblatt</emph> (October 16, 1894) found in the Jaskewitz Papers, he died in 1883. The <emph render="italic">Grosses Sängerlexikon</emph> by K.J. Kutsch and Leo Riemens (München : K.G. Saur, 1997), from which most of the foregoing biographical information is drawn, states that he died on March 8, 1888.</p>
      </bioghist>
